column5: WITH IT BEING MIGHTY LATE IN THE SEASON MY QUEST TO FIND SOME STEEL IN THE RIVERS WAS STILL THERE!!! HAD A FEW HRS YESTERDAY AND THE WIFE SENT ME PACKIN  LOL HIT A FEW SPOTS BUT EVENTUALLY FOUND WHAT I WAS LOOKIN FOR !!!! WENT 2/3 !! EXTREMELY WELL CONSIDERING WATER TEMPS AND TIME OF YR!!! NOW BACK TO PACKING AND WORK COULDNT THINK OF A BETTER WAY TO BREAK IN MY NEW FISHING DIGI!!!!!!

Great job out there!!  Bly and I tried a bit of night time fishing...had a few hits...saw a flash of chrome and that was about it.  Bly pulled in a nice 11 inch rock bass...hit a fly....LOL.  We're hoping to catch one or two more...maybe today...gotta use up about 10 roe bags...dont want them to go to waste.  Thanks for the pics bro....hope the moving and job still allows an hour or two for fishing!
Great job! I was thinking of heading out in the morning.... are you still getting them on roe? jigs? Thanks, Cheese
Nice going, you get a waterproof digital this time?
jigs life!!  and no caper not waterproof!!! was a gift!!! tx all
A couple nice one's CC and nice clear pic's...
